snippet.title: Weapons | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
There’s something wrong in Maybrook. #WeaponsMovie - only in theaters August 8. 

From New Line Cinema and Zach Cregger, the wholly original mind behind Barbarian, comes a new horror/thriller: Weapons.

When all but one child from the same class mysteriously vanish on the same night at exactly the same time, a community is left questioning who or what is behind their disappearance.

The film stars Josh Brolin, Julia Garner, Alden Ehrenreich, Austin Abrams, Cary Christopher, with Benedict Wong, and Amy Madigan.

Cregger directs from his own screenplay, and also produces alongside Roy Lee, Miri Yoon, J.D. Lifshitz and Raphael Margules, with Michelle Morrissey and Josh Brolin executive producing. The filmmaker’s creative team behind the camera includes director of photography Larkin Seiple, production designer Tom Hammock, editor Joe Murphy and costume designer Trish Sommerville. The music is by Ryan Holladay, Hays Holladay and Zach Cregger.

New Line Cinema Presents a Subconscious/Vertigo Entertainment/Boulderlight Pictures Production, a Zach Cregger Film, Weapons. It will be distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures, and released in theaters and IMAX nationwide on August 8, 2025, and internationally beginning in August 2025.

snippet.title: James May has bought a new car!
snippet.description:
I've bought a new car - and here’s my road test - conducted in the rain, between Shaftesbury and Salisbury, where there happens to be an excellent pub selling a range of delicious home-cooked meals and my gin. It’s a car that breaks when you clean it - but it’s also part of what made me complete as a human being. Also it’s very useful for running errands - such as buying my gin in Waitrose. Which you can now do too, in any car you want.

snippet.title: Wives just seem to disappear around this former cop - the Dark Secrets of Officer Drew Peterson
snippet.description:
#truecrimecommunity #drewpeterson 

Everyone in Bolingbrook, Illinois thought Sgt. Drew Peterson was just a real solid guy. He once owned a local bar, he was a cop and even had connections to the government. 

But his good guy routine was shattered when his wife turned up dead and his next wife just... disappeared one day. Once people started asking questions and national news outlets got involved... what they uncovered was twisted.

Now... this story first aired as a podcast exclusive. So go check out MMM wherever you get podcasts because, in case you didn't know, there are some episodes over there that you can't find on my YouTube!

But what this version has the pod exclusive doesn't - cool visuals! I'm talking documents from the investigation, interview footage and courtroom sketches.

So today... in a special episode I'm calling a Video Pod... we're talking about the shocking story of Drew Peterson: a man who used his badge, reputation, and connections to hide in plain sight. Until he couldn't. 

Also, let me know who you want me to discuss next time. I hope you have a great rest of your week. Make good choices, and I'll be seeing you very soon.
xo 
Bailey Sarian

snippet.title: Police give latest update on car attack at festival in Vancouver
snippet.description:
At least 11 people have been killed and several others injured after a vehicle struck a crowd at a street festival in Vancouver, according to police.

Deputy chief constable Steve Rai of the Vancouver Police Department provided an update, revealing that the alleged driver has a history of interactions with both law enforcement and healthcare professionals.

He also stated: "While I'm confident the joint risk assessment and public safety plan was sound, we will be working with our partners at the city of Vancouver to review all of the circumstances surrounding the planning of this event."

Read more: https://news.sky.com/story/several-killed-after-vehicle-drives-into-crowd-at-street-festival-police-in-vancouver-say-13356722

snippet.title: #2 ROCKETS at #7 WARRIORS | FULL GAME 4 HIGHLIGHTS | April 28, 2025
snippet.description:
The Warriors defeated the Rockets, 109-106 tonight in Golden State. Jimmy Butler III led the Warriors 27 points to go with 6 assists and 5 rebounds for the Warriors, while Brandin Podziemski contributed 26 points and 6 three pointers and 5 rebounds. Alperen Sengun finished with a team-high 31 points along with 10 rebounds 5 assists and 2 steals for the Rockets in the losing effort. The Warriors lead the series 3-1.

Maglock contains amorphous silica silicate, which differs significantly from crystalline silica associated with silicosis and other lung conditions.
